Document: Timer
Path: godot/classes/class_timer.rst
Summary: Describes the properties available for the Timer node in Godot Engine.

Properties
- autostart (bool): If true, the Timer will start automatically when it enters the scene tree. Default: false.
- ignore_time_scale (bool): If true, the Timer will not be affected by the global time scale. Default: false.
- one_shot (bool): If true, the Timer will stop after timing out once. Default: false.
- paused (bool): If true, the Timer will not count down.
- process_callback (TimerProcessCallback): Specifies when the Timer's timeout signal should be emitted. Default: 1.
- time_left (float): The remaining time in seconds until the Timer times out.
- wait_time (float): The time in seconds the Timer waits before timing out. Default: 1.0.
